.TH WEBSOCKET_DESTROY 3 "2026-06-24" "libhttp2 0.1.0" "libhttp2 Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
websocket_destroy, websocket_current_state \- cleanup and state query
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <websocket.h>

void websocket_destroy(websocket_ctx_t *ctx);
ws_state_t websocket_current_state(const websocket_ctx_t *ctx);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B websocket_destroy
releases all resources associated with the context (event queue, fragment buffer, ctx itself). NULL-safe.

.B websocket_current_state
returns the current ws_state_t (IDLE, OPEN, CLOSING, CLOSED, ERROR) or WS_STATE_ERROR if ctx is NULL.
.SH RETURN VALUES
current_state returns the enum value (no error codes).
.SH SEE ALSO
websocket_create(3), websocket_reset(3), libhttp2(3)
.SH NOTES
After destroy the pointer must not be used. Reset allows reuse of the allocation. State queries are safe for diagnostics.